-- Bayern Closes on Bundesliga Leader Dortmund; Milan Ties Catania
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-03-31T18:26:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-31/bayern-closes-on-bundesliga-leader-dortmund-milan-ties-catania.html
Bayern Munich  beat Nuremburg 1-0 to
pull within three points of first-place Dortmund in German
soccer’s Bundesliga.  Arjen Robben  scored in the 69th minute as Bayern gained on
Dortmund, which drew 4-4 last night with Stuttgart. Bayern
visits Dortmund on April 11.  AC Milan tied Catania 1-1 to extend its lead in Italy’s
Serie A to five points over Juventus, which plays Napoli
tomorrow. Milan’s Robinho opened the scoring in the 35th minute
and Catania’s Nicolas Spolli scored in the 57th minute.  Lee McCulloch’s goal in the 89th minute gave Rangers a 2-1
win over Motherwell in the Scottish Premier League. Rangers
moved six points ahead of Motherwell in the race for second
place and denied Celtic, which has a 15-point lead, a chance to
clinch the title tomorrow at St. Johnstone.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
